# Netlify redirects.
# Order matters: existing files (prerendered route HTML, static assets) are
# served BEFORE any of these rules by Netlify's file-first resolution.
# Rules below only fire when no matching file exists.

# 1. Permanent redirect: /ru/company is a duplicate alias of /company.
/ru/company            /company            301!

# 2. SPA fallback: unknown routes reach the React app so React Router can
#    render NotFound. Prerendered HTML files are served first automatically
#    (Netlify file-based routing), so this does NOT shadow /en, /zh,
#    /company, /en/company, etc.
/*                     /index.html         200
